radiographic_examinations.findings: Lung bases are clear. The liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, ureters, stomach, and abdominal loops of small and large bowel are within normal limits. No intra or extrahepatic biliary duct dilatation. The abdominal aorta is normal caliber throughout. A circumaortic left renal vein is incidentally detected. No pathologically enlarged mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymph nodes are demonstrated. No free air or free fluid. The appendix is dilated up to 11 mm with wall thickening and does not fill with oral contrast material. No significant periappendiceal fat stranding is demonstrated, and there is no evidence of abscess or extraluminal gas to suggest perforation. The remaining pelvic loops of bowel are within normal limits without evidence of obstruction. The rectum is normal. The distal ureters, bladder, ovaries, and uterus are unremarkable. No pelvic free fluid. No pelvic or inguinal lymphadenopathy is identified. 2 screws are seen within the right iliac wing. No concerning lytic or sclerotic osseous abnormalities are demonstrated.
